fields.name: Tooth Extraction
fields.description: This is the removal of a tooth from its socket in the bone. It is necessary when a tooth is too damaged to be repaired with a filling or crown, or if the mouth is crowded (like with wisdom teeth).

fields.name: Dental Implants
fields.description: An implant is a long-term solution for missing teeth. A metal post (usually titanium) is surgically positioned into the jawbone beneath the gum line to act as an artificial tooth root. Once the bone heals around the metal post (osseointegration), a replacement tooth (crown) is mounted onto it.

fields.name: Cleaning
fields.description: Professional dental cleaning to remove plaque and tartar buildup, promoting oral health and preventing gum disease.

fields.name: Consultation
fields.description: Initial dental examination and consultation to assess oral health, discuss concerns, and develop treatment plans.

fields.notes: My teeth hurts so bad doc help me please!
